\f0\b\fs58 \cf0 Hollandaise Sauce
\f1\b0\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Serves:  8 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 Ingredients
\f1\b0\fs46 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 12 tablespoons unsalted butter (1 1/2 sticks)\
4 extra-large egg yolks, at room temperature\
3 tablespoons freshly squeezed lemon juice\
Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper\
2 pinches of cayenne pepper\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 Directions
\f1\b0\fs46 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Melt the butter in a small sauce pan. Place the egg yolks, lemon juice, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 3/4 teaspoon pepper and cayenne in the jar of a blender. Blend for 15 seconds. With the blender running, slowly pour the hot butter into the blender and blend for 30 seconds, until the sauce is thick. \
